```cpp
#include <iostream>

// Function to find the nth Fibonacci number using recursion
int fibonacci(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) {
        return n;
    } else {
        return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
    }
}

int main() {
    int n;
    std::cout << "Enter the value of n: ";
    std::cin >> n;

    int nthFibonacci = fibonacci(n);
    std::cout << "The " << n << "th Fibonacci number is: " << nthFibonacci << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

To use this program, simply compile and run it, then enter the value of n when prompted. The program will then calculate and display the nth Fibonacci number using the recursive `fibonacci()` function. Keep in mind that this recursive approach is not very efficient for large values of n, as it involves a lot of repeated calculations. For larger values, an iterative approach or memoization technique would be more efficient.

